<chapter>
<title>Tips and Tricks</title>
 <section> 
<body>

  <p><b>Renaming Files</b></p>

  <p>Often files need to be converted from uppercase to lowercase.
    Sometimes this is a side effect of moving from case-insensitive
    file systems to case-sensitive ones.</p>

  <p>Here's a quick shell command that will convert everything in the
    current directory from uppercase to lowercase.</p>
  <pre><i>for n in *; do mv $n `echo $n | tr '[:upper:]' '[:lower:]'`; done</i></pre>
    

</body>
</section>
